Defendant Precious Harrell appeared by video.  Attorney Dawn Marie Rablin in court for Precious Harrell.  Prosecuting attorney Brad Alan Vorpahl in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
Defendant has attended all office contacts and is in compliance with the terms of the agreement. In order to receive the benefits of the agreement, the defendant needs to complete the terms of the agreement. Case adjourned to Branch 17.
Review hearing scheduled for January 23, 2023 at 09:00 am.
Received and Filed. DPA Supervision Report 10.10.2022
Received and Filed. Notice of competition
Received and Filed. Public Defender Order Appointing Counsel

Defendant Precious Harrell in court with attorney Connor Romenesko.  Annie Louk appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Case in court for deferred prosecution agreement hearing.  Court holds colloquy with the defendant regarding her right to appear in person before the Court when changing her plea. Court finds the defendant knowingly, intelligently and voluntarily waives her right to appear in person before the Court and agrees to proceed electronically via Zoom/live on Dacast.  

Parties are prepared to enter into a deferred prosecution agreement.  Deferred Agreement, Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, Addendum to Plea, and Elements/Jury Instructions received and filed.  The Court reviewed the agreement with the defendant.

AS TO COUNT 1:  
Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights and entered a plea of GUILTY.  Defendant was examined as to the plea.  Parties stipulate to the Criminal Complaint as a factual basis to sustain the guilty plea.  Defendant further advised that if she is not a US citizen deportation is possible.  Court found the defendant guilty as charged in the Criminal Complaint.  Court approved the deferred agreement and WITHHELD entry of judgment of conviction.  

Case adjourned for review hearing in Branch 21.   Pursuant to Chief Judge Directive 22-04, parties are hereby notified that effective July 30, 2022 this case will be assigned to branch 17, Judge Carolina Stark, in Room 400 of the Courthouse.  Review hearing scheduled for October 10, 2022 at 08:30 am.
